        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Jackson KY</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Confluence, or 7 miles north of Hyden, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hazard, Avawam, Confluence, Dryhill, Shoal, Toulouse, Kaliopi, Mosley
Bend, Krypton, and Buckhorn Lake S.P..

THIS INCLUDES Hal Rogers Parkway between mile markers 48 and 57.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
